/*
Since the full-scale db SPL of the Bricklet is at 120dB, while the
full 24 bit resolution can result in 20*log_10(2^24) = 144dB and there is additional
loss because the microphone will not be perfectly centered around the whole
etc we have to calculate an offset.

We did this by comparing the Bricklet output to a UT352 Sound Pressure Level meter
with +-1.5dB accuracy. We tested with 1m distance at 1kHz with different volumes:

    UT352   SPL Bricklet
1   38,7    47,83
2   44,6    53,59
3   50,5    58,01
4   56,3    64,15
5   60,2    67,28
6   63,8    71,47
7   70      77,85
8   75,4    82,96
9   79      86,63

The average offset is 7.9dB.
*/
const uint16_t lut_dba_offset = 79; // 7.9 dB


